Feature 1: Add Other Users as Friends
Users should be able to send friend requests to other users, accept incoming friend requests, cancel pending requests, and remove existing friends.

Test accounts: testuser1, testuser2

Initial condition: Both accounts exist in the database. The users are not already friends.

Acceptance Criteria
A logged-in user can send a friend request to another user.
The receiving user can accept the friend request.
Once accepted, both users appear as friends.
A user can remove an existing friend.
The app should not allow duplicate friend relationships.
UAT Test Cases

Feature 1 test 1: Send Friend Request

Procedure:
Log in as testuser1.
Navigate to testuser2’s profile.
Click the add friend button.
Observe the friend status.

Expected result: The button/status changes to show that the request is pending.  A pending friend request is created in the database.

Actual result: Works as expected

Feature  1  Test 2: Accept Friend Request

Procedure:
Log out of testuser1.
Log in as testuser2.
Navigate to the friend requests area or testuser1’s profile.
Accept the friend request.

Expected result:
The request status changes from pending to accepted.
 Both users are now listed as friends.

Actual result: Works as expected, but the request is easily missed so make it more noticable


Feature 1 Test  3: Remove Friend

Procedure:
Log in as either testuser1 or testuser2.
Navigate to the other user’s profile.
Click the unfriend/remove friend button.

Expected result:
The friendship is removed for both users.
 The users no longer appear as friends.

Actual result: Works as expected


